Title : Ray Danniels
Text : {{Use Canadian English|date=February 2015}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}}
{{distinguish|Ray Daniels}}
'''Ray Danniels''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] music executive, [[record producer]], and [[talent manager]].  He's the founder of SRO (Standing Room Only) Management group, as well as independent record labels [[Moon Records (Canada)|Moon Records]] and [[Anthem Records]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Anthem|url=http://www.anthementertainmentgroup.com/sro/anthem/about_anthem.php|work=Anthem Entertainment Group home page|accessdate=23 April 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141210082313/http://www.anthementertainmentgroup.com/sro/anthem/about_anthem.php|archivedate=10 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>  He first rose to prominence as the manager of the Canadian band [[Rush (band)|Rush]] and later served as the manager of [[Extreme (band)|Extreme]], [[King's X]], and [[Van Halen]]. His sister-in-law Kelly Carter was married to [[Alex Van Halen]]. He was instrumental in bringing in [[Gary Cherone]], former lead singer of Extreme, to replace [[Sammy Hagar]] as lead singer of Van Halen.<ref>{{cite web|last=Greene|first=Andy|title=Gary Cherone Reflects on his Three-Year Stint In Van Halen|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/gary-cherone-reflects-on-his-three-year-stint-in-van-halen-20120210|work=[[Rolling Stone (magazine)|Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=23 April 2014}}</ref>

He was awarded the [[Walt Grealis Special Achievement Award]] at the [[Juno Awards of 2015|2015 Juno Awards]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://junoawards.ca/2015/01/ray-danniels-honoured-walt-grealis-special-achievement-award-2015-juno-awards/ | title=Renowned Music Executive Acknowledged for His Myriad Contributions to the Canadian Music Industry | publisher=CARAS | date=29 January 2015 | accessdate=10 February 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150211052631/http://junoawards.ca/2015/01/ray-danniels-honoured-walt-grealis-special-achievement-award-2015-juno-awards/ | archivedate=11 February 2015 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>

